content.description: This splitter begins with wide fists to stacks on sharp granite, then thins to hands as the angle of the climb eases up. The climb finishes with a dirty flared roof that is significantly harder than the rest of the route. After you pull the roof, anchors are on the wall to the left. Make sure your rope isn't tangled if you're throwing it as stuck rope potential is high.
content.protection: Doubles from #1-#4 C4s. Didn't have a 5 or 6 but I think they could be useful. 60m Rope
content.location: Scramble up the boulder field guarding the east face of the dome. After that, bushwhack your way to the base of the crack, which is the first on the right after ducking under the little rock arch made by a boulder leaning against the cliff.

content.description: Start in Crack directly left of Wikiup. Start in #5's OW that quickly turns into rough #6 terrain. Stacking is definitely the move on this climb. Tape up and bring thick clothing. Route can be toproped with a 60m. This is one of my favorite climbs I've done out here, burly/grainy/painful, every thing you want in a stellar OW climb.
content.protection: doubles 4 - 6 extra 5 and 6 may be handy.
content.location: Either Hike from Meltdown parking or find the off road a little further down the Ranch road leading towards Tau-gu dome. 4x4 driving is suggested for the side road and probably cuts 15 to 20 minutes off the approach. Bushwhack until you reach the cracks.
